likewise /ˈlaɪkˌwaɪz/

1. ADV You use likewise when you are comparing two methods, states, or situations and saying that they are similar. 同样地 

例： What is fair for homeowners likewise should be fair to businesses. 对私房业主公平的，同样也该对商家公平。 

2. ADV If you do something and someone else does likewise , they do the same or a similar thing. 照样地 [ADV after v] 

例： He lent money, made donations and encouraged others to do likewise. 他把钱借出、捐出，并鼓励其他人这么做。

</div>

